Phase 1 Readme

Nick Ferrari and Mason Coleman

For phase one, we implemented three new functions: traverseHelper(), 
stripNonAlphaNum(), and traverseDirectory(). 

stripNonAlphaNum(): This function is used to find a string that starts
and ends with an alphanumeric character to be used as a query. It first
starts iterating through each character at the front of the string to 
find the starting alphanumeric character. and then iterates from the back
to find the last alphanumeric character. The function then concatenates the
original string to extract just the characters including and between these
bounds, and returns the string.

traverseDirectory(): This function takes in a directory and constructs an
FSTree rooted at that directory. It then gets the node of the root, and passes
that root, along with its name, to traverseHelper.

traverseHelper(): This function takes in a node and a string containting the 
current filepath, and recursively goes through every subdirectory of a starting
node and prints it to terminal. 